00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,200
A tiny device that changed everything: the transistor.

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:08,000
Transistors amplify and switch electrical signals, forming the backbone of digital computing.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:10,800
Before transistors, computers were massive and unreliable.

4
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:11,200
Now?

5
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:12,800
They're in your pocket!

6
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:18,400
Invented in 1947, it marked the dawn of the electronics age, sparking a revolution.

7
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:21,600
From smartphones to supercomputers, the transistor is everywhere.

8
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,600
Imagine a world without it!

